      "sourceRef": "kontourai-flow-agents-289/evidence.json",
      "excerptOrSummary": "Fold of remaining gates + manual scratch probes (non-manifest, session-local): npm run build clean (tsc exit 0); bash evals/run.sh static 65/65 pass (0 fail); bash evals/integration/test_actor_identity.sh 11/11 pass; bash evals/integration/test_liveness_heartbeat.sh 43/43 pass. Scratch probes on a throwaway artifact-root (built CLI, no git worktree ops): (a) the four F2' fuzz-escape classes each died pre-mutation with the expected per-component diagnostic and wrote no session artifact; (b) a valid nested --branch (feature/nested/deep-path_v2.1) was recorded verbatim in state.json and independently passed the real git check-ref-format binary; (c) actors unknown / unknown. / .unknown each derived a distinct disambiguated branch (agent/unknown-b23a6a/*, agent/unknown-4dd633/*, agent/unknown-2a9676/*), each git-valid, and the same three hashes reproduced identically on a second ensure-session run against fresh slugs (deterministic); (d) regression checks all held: derived-branch round-trip identical across state.json/deliver.md/current.json, --branch verbatim recording, no-rederive on takeover by a different actor, F1 trailing-dot slug still derives a git-valid branch, and a garbage --actor (:::) died fail-closed with zero artifacts written. AC1/AC6/AC8 spot-checked directly against schemas/workflow-state.schema.json, the four SKILL.md files, and docs/workflow-usage-guide.md — no regression from iteration-1 baseline.",
